HEADWORD: Metrification
<hw>Met`ri*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Composition in metrical form; versification.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act or process of converting the standard system
of units of a country to those of the metric system;
metrication.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metrify</ent>⟦br⟧
